 PLAY AUDIO FILE IN BACKGROUND USING POWERSHELL:----->>>
 
 Invoke-Command -ComputerName RemoteComputerName -ScriptBlock {
    Add-Type -AssemblyName presentationCore
    $mediaPlayer = New-Object system.windows.media.mediaplayer
    $mediaPlayer.Open('C:\Users\sahil\Music\abc\King .mp3')
    $mediaPlayer.Play()
} -AsJob


NOTE: ---

Replace RemoteComputerName with the actual name or IP address of the remote computer, and 'C:\path\to\your\file.mp3' with the path to the MP3 file on the remote system. The -AsJob parameter runs the command as a background job.
